				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "4f70debc-80b3-4f4a-9f04-c95ebf5154cb")
	)
	(text_box "INA226 Shunt and VBUS Connection Options - Design Note\n\nThis design uses the INA226 to measure current and power on USB VBUS rails via a series shunt resistor. The INA226 has two different measurement inputs that must be understood separately.\n\nShunt Measurement (VIN+ and VIN−)\n\nThe shunt resistor is always placed in series with the rail being monitored.\n\n• VIN+ connects to the upstream side of the shunt (closer to the source or connector)\n• VIN− connects to the downstream side of the shunt (closer to the load)\n\nThis connection determines the direction and magnitude of the measured current and must not be changed.\n\nBus Voltage Measurement (VBUS)\n\nVBUS is a single ended voltage sense input referenced to GND. It does not power the device. VBUS can be connected to different points depending on what voltage and power meaning is desired.\n\nOption A - VBUS = VIN− (Load Side Voltage)\nVBUS tied to VIN− measures the voltage delivered to the circuit after the shunt.\nReported power represents power actually delivered to the downstream load.\nThis is the recommended and implemented option in this design.\n\nOption B - VBUS = VIN+ (Source Side Voltage)\nVBUS tied to VIN+ measures the source or connector voltage before the shunt.\nReported power represents power drawn from the source, including shunt losses.\nThis may be preferred when characterising USB port loading."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
